About TechTatva 25

TechTatva is the annual technical festival of Manipal Institute of Technology, Manipal, celebrating innovation, creativity, and technological excellence. Conducted over a period of four days, including prestigious competitions, hackathons, and technical workshops, the fest is a convergence of brilliant minds and cutting-edge ideas.

From Robotics and AI to Cybersecurity, Web Development, and Machine Learning, TechTatva showcases the best of technical talent. Every year, thousands of students from colleges across the country, as well as international participants, come together to make TechTatva one of the largest platforms for technical innovation and knowledge exchange.

Our Legacy

TechTatva has been the cornerstone of technical innovation at Manipal Institute of Technology since its inception. What started as a small gathering of tech enthusiasts has evolved into one of the most prestigious technical festivals in the country.

Over the years, TechTatva has witnessed groundbreaking projects, revolutionary ideas, and the birth of countless innovations that have shaped the future of technology. The festival continues to inspire generations of engineers and technologists, fostering a culture of innovation and excellence that defines MIT's commitment to technological advancement.

FAQ
Can students from non-MAHE colleges participate in TechTatva?
Only students from non-MAHE engineering colleges are allowed to participate in TechTatva.
Whats the difference between the flagship and the generalpass?
The flagship pass gives you access to register for both flagship and general events, while the general pass only allows you to register for general events.
Can I upgrade from the general pass to the flagship pass even if I bought Combo 1
Yes, you can upgrade by paying the difference between Combo 1 and Combo 2.
I tried to log in as MAHE, but my enrollment number is not found.
Please recheck your enrollment number. If your branch was changed, please try using the old registration number.
I logged in as MAHE, and my enrollment number is recognised, but I cannot recognize the number I am getting OTP to.
Please recheck your enrollment number. If that is correct, and the system is sending OTP to some number, please check if the number displayed is of your parent or guardian. If that isn't the case, please log in to your SLcM, go to Admissions Profile, go to address, and change your present details phone number to the desired phone number. Wait 24 hours before trying to sign up.
What should I do if I make the payment, and it's not reflected on the website?
If payment is debited, the website will update in 48 hours, else you will get a refund automatically.
What is the cancellation and refund policy for all purchases?
No refunds are provided once a purchase is confirmed.
Is the standup for everyone?
Standup is for MIT students only.
Offline ticket sales
There will be no offline sales for any of the passes.
